ssinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-giving-up-medical-care-cant-afford-costs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20extremely%20understanding%20and%20supportive%20employers%2C%20we%20did%20not%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20losing%20our%20jobs%20or%20accumulating%20medical%20debt.%20Nevertheless%2C%20we%20began%20to%20fear%20a%20reality%20where%20we%20did%20not%20have%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22480e4d7f-60e7-4697-9d40-cdbc3b1fa1a0%5C%22%3EWe%20switched%20clinics%20and%20I%20got%20pregnant%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20switch%20clinics%20after%20our%20first%20told%20us%20there%20was%20nothing%20left%20that%20they%20could%20do.%20At%20the%20new%20clinic%2C%20I%20had%20laparoscopic%20surgery%20to%20remove%20endometriosis%20lesions%20on%20my%20organs%20and%20to%20perform%20ovarian%20diathermy.%20The%20latter%20is%20a%20procedure%20during%20which%20your%20ovaries%20are%20lasered%20to%20lower%20your%20ovarian%20reserve%20with%20the%20hopes%20of%20the%20ovaries%20producing%20fewer%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fhow-many-eggs-does-a-woman-have%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher-quality%20eggs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221125%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20in%20hospital%20after%20fertility%20treatment%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667da73f40cf2af6e4f656ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22844%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20worries%20about%20what%20it%20will%20take%20to%20have%20another%20child%2C%20both%20financially%20and%20physically.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20cycles%20later%2C%20as%20we%20waited%20on%20my%20period%20to%20begin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-i-freeze-my-eggs-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eegg%20retrieval%3C%2Fa%3E%20three%2C%20I%20found%20out%20I%20was%20pregnant.%20Terrified%20and%20overjoyed%2C%20we%20cautiously%20navigated%20a%20surprisingly%20uncomplicated%20pregnancy.%20After%20nine%20long%20and%20anxious%20months%2C%20I%20had%20a%20whirlwind%20four-hour%20labor%2C%20and%20we%20met%20our%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20recovery%20room%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20both%20began%20sharing%20anxieties%20about%20how%20we%20needed%20to%20structure%20our%20lives%20to%20have%20another%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa029946-9349-416f-9c11-fd4016cfb8b8%5C%22%3EI%20have%20anxiety%20about%20trying%20for%20another%20child%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20this%20is%20not%20my%20reality%20alone.%20I%20have%20spoken%20with%20people%20in%20various%20support%20groups%20I%20have%20joined%20throughout%20my%20infertility%20and%20pregnancy%20journey%20about%20the%20next%20child%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%20child%20anxiety%20is%20a%20fear%20of%20being%20retraumatized.%20It%20is%20a%20scale%20where%20we%20weigh%20the%20benefits%20of%20giving%20our%20child%20a%20sibling%20and%20the%20joys%20of%20having%20another%20child%20to%20love%20against%20the%20crushing%20reality%20of%20infertility%20and%20its%20treatments.%20It%20is%20figuring%20out%20how%20far%20you%20are%20willing%20to%20go%20into%20ART%20again%20and%20what%20the%20limits%20would%20look%20like.%20My%20surgery's%20effectiveness%20is%20typically%20two%20years%2C%20and%20over%20nine%20months%20have%20already%20been%20spent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20recently%20postpartum%2C%20it%20also%20feels%20unfair.%20My%20body%20has%20not%20been%20my%20own%20for%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20of%20treatment%20and%20nine%20months%20of%20pregnancy.%20But%20here%20I%20am%2C%20trying%20to%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20the%20career%20anxiety.%20Will%20we%20have%20infertility%20benefits%3F%20After%20my%20parental%20leave%2C%20I%20switched%20to%20remote%20work%20and%20lost%20the%20wonderful%20health%