0Trump's%20lawyers%20raised%20other%20instances%20where%20they%20say%20%26quot%3Bofficial%20acts%26quot%3B%20were%20improperly%20used%20at%20trial%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20one%20is%20testimony%20by%20Trump's%20former%20communications%20director%2C%20Hicks%2C%20who%20described%20to%20jurors%20Trump's%20reaction%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%2C%20when%20news%20of%20Trump's%20hush-money%20payment%20to%20porn%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels%20first%20broke%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20wanted%20to%20know%20how%20it%20was%20playing%2C%26quot%3B%20Hicks%20told%20the%20jury%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20news%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20Mr.%20Trump's%20opinion%20was%20it%20was%20better%20to%20be%20dealing%20with%20it%20now%2C%20and%20that%20it%20would%20have%20been%20bad%20to%20have%20that%20story%20come%20out%20before%20the%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20jurors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20devastating%2C%26quot%3B%20Steinglass%2C%20the%20prosecutor%2C%20said%20in%20closing%20arguments%20of%20Hick's%20testimony%2C%20noting%20that%20it%20firmly%20linked%20the%20hush-money%20payment%20to%20the%20presidential%20election%2C%20a%20legally-vital%20connection%20Trump%20had%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParadis%20said%20prosecutors%20may%20now%20find%20themselves%20battling%20with%20the%20defense%20over%20how%20much%20of%20Hicks'%20Oval%20Office%20conversation%20with%20Trump%20concerned%20an%20official%20topic%2C%20and%20must%20therefore%20be%20banned%20as%20testimony.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20is%20more%20likely%2C%20appeals%20judges%20down%20the%20line%20%E2%80%94%20may%20bar%20any%20prosecutorial%20use%20of%20the%20Hicks-Trump%20conversation%20merely%20because%20some%20of%20it%20could%20have%20touched%20on%20official%20acts%2C%20Paradis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20is%20also%20signaling%20that%20it%20will%20challenge%20the%20use%20of%20certain%20incriminating%20tweets%2C%20including%20one%20from%20May%2C%202018%2C%20in%20which%20Trump%20again%20referred%20to%20his%20payments%20to%20Cohen%20as%20%26quot%3Breimbursement%26quot%3B%20for%20%26quot%3Ba%20non-disclosure%20agreement%2C%26quot%3B%20AKA%20hush%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20May%202018%20tweet%20by%20then-President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20in%20which%20he%20acknowledges%20that%20Michael%20Cohen%20received%20%26quot%3Breimbursement%26quot%3B%20for%20%20a%20%26quot%3Bnon-disclosure%20agreement.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664fdef3a961b37edf398b44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22658%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETrump%20tweeted%20about%20a%20non-disclosure%20agreement%20in%202018.%3Cp%3EManhattan%20District%20Attorney's%20Office%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20and%20other%20tweets%20the%20defense%20is%20terming%20%26quot%3Bofficial%26quot%3B%20were%20sent%20from%20Trump's%20personal%20Twitter%20account%2C%20and%20concern%2C%20as%20Trump%20himself%20put%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20private%20contract%26quot%3B%20involving%20a%20very%20private%20alleged%20encounter%20with%20Daniels.%20It%20may%20be%20hard%20for%20Trump%20to%20argue%20the%20tweets%20were%20in%20any%20way%20%26quot%3Bofficial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20defense%20wrote%20Tuesday%20that%20it%20will%20challenge%20the%20prosecution's%20use%20of%20phone%20records%20%26quot%3Breflecting%20calls%20involving%20President%20Trump%20while%20he%20was%20in%20office.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20as%20records%20of%20both%20personal%20and%20business%20calls%2C%20this%20evidence%20contains%20a%20mix%20of%20official%20and%20unofficial%20acts%20that%20must%20now%20be%20parsed%20apart%20and%20argued%20over%20in%20front%20of%20Merchan%20and%20any%20appellate%20judges%20that%20subsequently%20get%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20People's%2081%2C%20prosecutors'%20best%20bet%20may%20be%20to%20argue%20that%20financial%20disclosure%20forms%20like%20this%20one%20are%20%26quot%3Bpersonnel%20documents%2C%26quot%3B%20Paradis%20said%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bwhich%2C%20in%20the%20bureaucracy%20of%20the%20federal%20government%20would%20likely%20be%20deemed%20'personal.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20whether%20that%20argument%20sinks%20or%20flies%20is%20anyone's%20guess%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20the%20thing%20about%20this%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20not%20come%20right%20out%20and%20say%20'the%20president%20is%20immune%20from%20all%20prosecution.'%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20it%20is%20more%20pernicious%20than%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20creates%20an%20immunity%20that%20is%20so%20ill-defined%20and%20so%20unmoored%20from%20any%20agreed-upon%20constitutional%20text%20or%20history%2C%20that%20there%20is%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20its%20outer%20limits%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20leaving%20so%20much%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20outer%20limits%20means%2C%20for%20all%20practical%20purposes%2C%20that%20those%20outer%20limits%20don't%20exist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpiece-of-evidence-can-now-scuttle-trump-hush-money-conviction-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719960710000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668480e41f0c1cd6d731063c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpiece-of-evidence-can-now-scuttle-trump-hush-money-conviction-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20the%20SCOTUS%20immunity%20decision%2C%20it%20may%20not%20take%20much%20to%20force%20a%20hush-money%20retrial.%20An%20ethics%20form%20the%20DA%20showed%20jurors%20in%20May%20might%20do%20the%20trick.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22litaliano%40insider.com%20(Laura%20Italiano)%22