%20a%20torpedo%20duel%20during%20a%20Baltic%20Sea%20training%20exercise%20last%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20crews%20of%20the%C2%A0Novorossiysk%20and%C2%A0Dmitrov%20also%20trained%20to%20track%20enemies%20and%20evade%20enemy%20attacks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Baltic%20Sea%20has%20been%20described%20as%20a%C2%A0%26quot%3BNATO%20lake%26quot%3B%20since%20Sweden%20and%20Finland%20joined%20the%20alliance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20Russian%20submarines%20recently%20fought%20a%20torpedo%20duel%2C%20conducting%20training%20that%20involved%20detecting%20enemies%2C%20evading%20attacks%2C%20and%20working%20combat%20maneuvers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exercises%20took%20place%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%2C%20waters%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BNATO%20lake%26quot%3B%20due%20to%20its%20waters%20being%20surrounded%20by%20NATO%20allies%20since%20Sweden%20and%20Finland%20ascended%20into%20the%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kilo-class%2C%20diesel-electric%20submarines%20Novorossiysk%20and%20Dmitrov%20held%20a%20training%20duel%20involving%20torpedo%20fire%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.ru%2Farmiya-i-opk%2F21199903%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20state-run%20media%20TASS%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20media%20outlet%20reported%20the%20training%20exercise%20on%20June%2025%2C%20citing%20the%20Russian%20navy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20following%20the%20completion%20of%20anti-submarine%20warfare%20maneuvers%2C%20the%20submarine%20Novorossiysk%20engaged%20the%20Dmitrov%20with%20a%20training%20torpedo%20without%20a%20warhead%2C%20the%20navy%20said%2C%20per%20TASS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20submarine%20crews%20also%20conducted%20several%20other%20exercises%20focused%20on%20detecting%20and%20tracking%20adversary%20submarines%2C%20evasion%2C%20and%20combat%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subs%20Novorossiysk%20and%20Dmitrov%20are%20representative%20of%20two%20of%20several%20variants%20of%20Russian%20Kilo-class%20submarines.%20The%20Novorossiysk%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20a%20project%20636.3%20sub%20and%20can%20launch%20Kalibr%20cruise%20missiles.%20636.3s%20are%20the%20most%20current%20Kilo-class%20subs%20being%20built.%20The%20Dmitrov%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20a%20project%20877%20sub%2C%20one%20of%20the%20original%20variants%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20subs%20are%20known%20for%20being%20relatively%20quiet%2C%20but%20the%20Novorossiysk%20and%20other%20project%20636.3%20subs%20are%20considered%20to%20be%20highly%20advanced%20and%20stealthy%20vessels.%20After%20wrapping%20up%20the%20torpedo%20training%2C%20the%20two%20Russian%20submarines%20went%20on%20to%20conduct%20other%20combat%20exercises%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%2C%20Russian%20media%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Various%20NATO%20warships%20sail%20in%20columns%20in%20the%20blue%20water%20of%20the%20Baltic%20Sea.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656771d1fd6200867dd09f02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221124%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShips%20from%20NATO%20navies%20sail%20in%20formation%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20during%20the%20exercise%20Baltic%20Operations%202023.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20Shawn%20Coover%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Baltic%20Sea%20area%20has%20seen%20geopolitical%20shifts%20since%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%20two%20years%20ago%20and%20neighboring%20Finland%20and%20Sweden%20joined%20NATO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20sometimes%20been%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BNATO%20lake%26quot%3B%20considering%20that%20eight%20of%20the%20nine%20countries%20bordering%20it%20are%20now%20members%20of%20the%20alliance.%20Russia%20is%20the%20only%20exception.%20That's%20a%20stark%20difference%20from%201990%2C%20when%20only%20two%20Baltic%20Sea%20countries%2C%20Denmark%20and%20Germany%2C%20were%20NATO%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BNATO%20lake%26quot%3B%20term%20has%20been%20debated%20and%20criticized%20as%20presumptuous%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fcommentary%2Fno-dont-call-baltic-nato-lake%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20experts%20calling%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bfatal%26quot%3B%20mistake%20as%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%20can%20be%20traversed%20by%20any%20seafaring%20nation%20and%20remains%20an%20important%20strategic%20front%20for%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Baltic%20Sea%20has%20become%20increasingly%20important%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chathamhouse.org%2F2024%2F04%2Fbaltic-sea-far-nato-lake-alliance-must-strengthen-its-defences%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENATO's%20military%20presence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Russia%20also%20sees%20the%20body%20of%20water%20as%20vital%20to%20its%20commercial%20shipping%2C%20oil%20exports%2C%20and%20trade%20from%20ports%20like%20St.%20Petersburg%20and%20Primorsk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20region%20is%20also%20home%20to%20increasing%20Russian%20anti-access%2Farea%20denial%20capabilities%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Kaliningrad%20area.%20These%20capabilities%20include%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20surface-to-air%20missiles%2C%20and%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20making%20the%20sea%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fresearch%2F2023%2F12%2Fis-the-baltic-sea-a-nato-lake%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrategically%20important%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20both%20Moscow%20and%20NATO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-submarines-fought-torpedo-duel-in-sea-surrounded-by-nato-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719949271000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6684235f1aace5b3ada3a1bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-submarines-fought-torpedo-duel-in-sea-surrounded