2%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BParasite%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3BKhatakhat%20Diwas%26quot%3B%3A%20PM%20Hits%20Back%20Amid%20Protests%20In%20Lok%20Sabha%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Opposition%20is%20back%20in%20strength%20in%20parliament%2C%20determined%20to%20make%20themselves%20heard.%20And%20they%20chose%20to%20do%20it%20today%2C%20when%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20rose%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20Motion%20of%20Thanks%20for%20the%20President's%20address.%20The%20result%20was%20a%20furious%20din%20that%20came%20close%20to%20the%20BJP%20protests%20of%202004%2C%20which%20stopped%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%20from%20introducing%20his%20Council%20of%20Ministers.%20PM%20Modi%2C%20though%2C%20laboured%20on%20through%20the%20uproar%20for%20over%20two%20hours%2C%20once%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20the%20Opposition%20would%20not%20relent.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ostensible%20reason%20for%20the%20Opposition%20protests%20was%20that%20the%20PM's%20speech%20came%20as%20a%20representative%20from%20Manipur%20was%20abruptly%20cut%20off.%20The%20Opposition%20has%20always%20maintained%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20had%20neglected%20the%20violence-hit%20state%2C%20not%20just%20failing%20to%20visit%20but%20also%20remaining%20silent%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20few%20MPs%20started%20protesting%20against%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla's%20refusal%2C%20the%20matter%20was%20taken%20up%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Opposition%20members.%20Soon%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20chamber%20rang%20with%20boos%20and%20slogans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20started%20speaking%2C%20the%20MPs%20stepped%20it%20up%20with%20louder%20slogans%20and%20table%20thumping.%20Chants%20of%20%26quot%3BManipur%2C%20Manipur%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3ETanashahi%20nahin%20chaleg%3C%2Fem%3Ei%20(We%20won't%20allow%20dictatorship)%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BJustice%20for%20Manipur%26quot%3B%20rang%20out%2C%20drawing%20an%20angry%20reprimand%20from%20the%20Speaker%2C%20directed%20at%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20understand%20the%20pain%20of%20some%20people.%20Even%20after%20spreading%20lies%2C%20they%20tasted%20defeat%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20finally%20said%20after%20waiting%20several%20times%20for%20the%20noise%20to%20subside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20of%20India%20have%20given%20us%20the%20opportunity%20to%20work%20for%20the%20third%20time.%20The%20people%20have%20given%20us%20a%20mandate.%20They%20saw%20our%20track%20record%20of%2010%20years.%2025%20crore%20came%20out%20of%20poverty.%20This%20never%20happened%20since%20Independence%2C%26quot%3B%20PM%20Modi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20expected%20hard-hitting%20political%20message%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20also%20spoke%20of%20minority%20appeasement%2C%20alleged%20corruption%20during%20the%20UPA%20government%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Article%20370%20and%20surgical%20strikes%20against%20terrorists%20--%20all%20amid%20the%20loud%20Opposition%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rebuttal%20to%20Congress's%20Rahul%20Gandhi's%20fiery%20speech%20yesterday%20--%20replete%20with%20repeated%20objections%20and%20angry%20outbursts%20from%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20his%20ministers%20--%20was%20sharp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20PM%20Modi%20continued%2C%20the%20volume%20of%20protests%20increased.%20Admonishing%20the%20Opposition%2C%20Mr%20Birla%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYesterday%2C%20I%20allowed%20you%20to%20speak%20for%2090%20minutes.%20No%20one%20stopped%20you.%20This%20is%20no%20way%20to%20behave%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Then%2C%20in%20an%20afterthought%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BPaanch%20saal%20aise%20nahin%20chalega%20(We%20cannot%20have%20five%20years%20of%20this)%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20not%20the%20first%20time%20Opposition%20protests%20had%20interrupted%20a%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20the%20House%20in%20this%20fashion.%20In%202004%2C%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%20could%20not%20introduce%20his%20Council%20of%20Ministers%20due%20to%20protests%20by%20the%20BJP.%20In%202008%2C%20he%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20reply%20to%20the%20debate%20on%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20his%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM%20Modi%2C%20speaking%20amid%20the%20deafening%20commotion%20today%2C%20soon%20started%20responding%20with%20barbs%20and%20mockery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTry%20to%20read%20the%20people's%20mandate.%20You%20are%20in%20the%20Opposition%20and%20you%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20Opposition%E2%80%A6%202024%20onwards%2C%20the%20Congress%20will%20be%20known%20as%20the%20'Parasite%20Congress'.%20They%20feed%20on%20the%20votes%20of%20other%20parties.%20They%20make%20alliances%20with%20them%20and%20cut%20their%20votes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20he%20parodied%20the%20Bollywood%20blockbuster%20Sholay%20--%20the%20sequence%20where%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20was%20'advocating'%20for%20his%20friend%20to%20a%20prospective%20mother-in-law.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EMausi%20ji%20teesri%20baar%20to%20haare%20hai%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fem%3E(Auntie%20he%20lost%20only%20for%20the%20third%20time)%C2%A0%20still%20a%20hero%20after%20winning%20zero%20seats%20in%2013%20states%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20mentioning%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20by%20name%2C%20PM%20Modi%20referred%20to%20him%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Ebalakbuddhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(the%20immature%20one)%26quot%3B%2C%20saying%20he%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20know%20his%20limits%26quot%3B%20and%20cited%20the%20incident%20when%20he%20was%20caught%20on%20camera%20in%20parliament%20winking%2C%20thought%20to%20be%20at%20then%20close%20aide%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20country%20is%20now%20feeling%20sorry%20that%20he%20is%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20PM%20Modi%20said.%20Then%2C%20in%20a%20jibe%2C%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20countr